Hash is a modern command line interpreter (shell) for Unix-like operating
systems. It provides a feature-rich alternative to traditional shells with
a focus on usability and modern development workflows.

Features include:
- Tab completion for commands, files, and directories
- Unix pipes and I/O redirection
- Command chaining with ;, &&, and ||
- Aliases and environment variables
- Command history with bash-compatible expansion (!, !!, !n)
- Customizable PS1 prompt with git integration
- Tilde and variable expansion
- .hashrc configuration file support
- Line editing with arrow keys, Ctrl+A/E, Ctrl+U/K, etc.

Hash aims for POSIX compliance while providing modern conveniences
expected by developers working with version control and build systems.
